page.title: 10Housing in Kinver
page.content: There is a variety of old and new housing. The High Street contains Georgian, Victorian and Edwardian Houses. Several have been recently restored. The Old Grammar School was built in the 17th century and is now a house. Many modern houses have been built in recent years and there are some small housing estates. Some of these are council houses but most houses in Kinver are privately owned. There are many more shops and banks than ten years ago and public houses are very common. The most interesting houses are the Holy Austin rock houses but these are in the next block to the west.
